cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.SD

The paper proposes a deep learning framework for processing time-series mobile sensing data. The use of convolutional and recurrent neural networks suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the framework to tasks such as car tracking and human activity recognition suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the focus on signal dynamics and temporal relationships suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SD).
